{"title_page": "List of places in London", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikimedia list article}}\n<!-- Compiled from http://toolserver.org/~para/cgi-bin/kmlexport?article=List_of_places_in_London&linksfrom=1&redir=google -->\nThis is an incomplete '''list of places in London''', England.\n{{TOC right}}\n\n==Geographic divisions and areas==\n\n===Neighbourhoods===\n{{main|List of districts of London}}\nAside from the City and the [[London]] boroughs themselves, all contemporary districts of London are informal designations; usually based or adapted from historic [[civil parish|parish]] or borough boundaries which were all abolished by 1965. [[London postal district|London postcode districts]] often have an influence over where a place is considered to be although they were not designed for that purpose. All London boroughs are divided into [[Ward (country subdivision)|ward]]s which often share the names of London districts, however, they rarely share the historic or commonly accepted contemporary boundaries of those places.\n\n===London boroughs===\n[[Greater London]] consists of the [[City of London]] and 32 [[London borough]]s, of which 12 are statutory [[Inner London]] boroughs and 20 are [[Outer London]] boroughs.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! class=\"unsortable\" |\n! [[London borough]] || [[Inner London|Inner]]/[[Outer London|Outer]] || [[London Plan|Sub-region]]<ref>London Assembly - ''[http://www.london.gov.uk/thelondonplan/caz/ London Plan: Sub-regions, CAZ and government growth area policies] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090713081553/http://www.london.gov.uk/thelondonplan/caz/ |date=2009-07-13 }}''</ref> || [[London Assembly constituencies|London Assembly]]<ref name=london_a>London Assembly - [http://www.london.gov.uk/assembly/constituencies.jsp London Assembly Constituency Information] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080117151444/http://www.london.gov.uk/assembly/constituencies.jsp |date=2008-01-17 }}. Retrieved on 22 February 2008.</ref>\n|-\n| [[File:LondonBarkingDagenham.svg|50px]] || [[London Borough of Barking and Dagenham|Barking and Dagenham]] ||  Outer || North East || [[City and East (London Assembly constituency)|City and East]]\n|-\n| [[File:LondonBarnet.svg|50px]] || [[London Borough of Barnet|Barnet]] || Outer || North || [[Barnet and Camden (London Assembly constituency)|Barnet and Camden]]\n|-\n| [[File:LondonBexley.svg|50px]] || [[London Borough of Bexley|Bexley]]  || Outer || South East || [[Bexley and Bromley (London Assembly constituency)|Bexley and Bromley]]\n|-\n| [[File:LondonBrent.svg|50px]] || [[London Borough of Brent|Brent]] || Outer || West || [[Brent and Harrow (London Assembly constituency)|Brent and Harrow]]\n|-\n| [[File:LondonBromley.svg|50px]] || [[London Borough of Bromley|Bromley]] ||  Outer || South East || Bexley and Bromley\n|-\n| [[File:LondonCamden.svg|50px]] || [[London Borough of Camden|Camden]] ||  Inner || North || Barnet and Camden\n|-\n| [[File:LondonCroydon.svg|50px]] || [[London Borough of Croydon|Croydon]]  || Outer || South West || [[Croydon and Sutton (London Assembly constituency)|Croydon and Sutton]]\n|-\n| [[File:LondonEaling.svg|50px]] || [[London Borough of Ealing|Ealing]] ||  Outer || West || [[Ealing and Hillingdon (London Assembly constituency)|Ealing and Hillingdon]]\n|-\n| [[File:LondonEnfield.svg|50px]] || [[London Borough of Enfield|Enfield]]  || Outer || North || [[Enfield and Haringey (London Assembly constituency)|Enfield and Haringey]]\n|-\n| [[File:LondonGreenwich.svg|50px]] || [[Royal Borough of Greenwich|Greenwich]]  || Inner \u2020 || South East || [[Greenwich and Lewisham (London Assembly constituency)|Greenwich and Lewisham]]\n|-\n| [[File:LondonHackney.svg|50px]] || [[London Borough of Hackney|Hackney]] || Inner || North || [[North East (London Assembly constituency)|North East]]\n|-\n| [[File:LondonHammersmithFulham.svg|50px]] || [[London Borough of Hammersmith and Fulham|Hammersmith and Fulham]]  |