 share the names of London districts, however, they rarely share the historic or commonly accepted contemporary boundaries of those places.\n\n===London boroughs===\n[[Greater London]] consists of the [[City of London]] and 32 [[London borough]]s, of which 12 are statutory [[Inner London]] boroughs and 20 are [[Outer London]] boroughs.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! class=\"unsortable\" |\n! [[London borough]] || [[Inner London|Inner]]/[[Outer London|Outer]] || [[London Plan|Sub-region]]<ref>London Assembly - ''[http://www.london.gov.uk/thelondonplan/caz/ London Plan: Sub-regions, CAZ and government growth area policies] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090713081553/http://www.london.gov.uk/thelondonplan/caz/ |date=2009-07-13 }}''</ref> || [[London Assembly constituencies|London Assembly]]<ref name=london_a>London Assembly - [http://www.london.gov.uk/assembly/constituencies.jsp London Assembly Constituency Information] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080117151444/http://www.london.gov.uk/assembly/constituencies.jsp |date=2008-01-17 }}. Retrieved on 22 February 2008.</ref>\n|-\n| [[File:LondonBarkingDagenham.svg|50px]] || [[London Borough of Barking and Dagenham|Barking and Dagenham]] ||  Outer || North East || [[City and East (London Assembly constituency)|City and East]]\n|-\n| [[File:LondonBarnet.svg|50px]] || [[London Borough of Barnet|Barnet]] || Outer || North || [[Barnet and Camden (London Assembly constituency)|Barnet and Camden]]\n|-\n| [[File:LondonBexley.svg|50px]] || [[London Borough of Bexley|Bexley]]  || Outer || South East || [[Bexley and Bromley (London Assembly constituency)|Bexley and Bromley]]\n|-\n| [[File:LondonBrent.svg|50px]] || [[London Borough of Brent|Brent]] || Outer || West || [[Brent and Harrow (London Assembly constituency)|Brent and Harrow]]\n|-\n| [[File:LondonBromley.svg|50px]] || [[London Borough of Bromley|Bromley]] ||  Outer || South East || Bexley and Bromley\n|-\n| [[File:LondonCamden.svg|50px]